# Competitive Feature Matrix

When the user wants to compare competitor features, run a feature gap analysis,
survey the major players in a product segment, decide what to build next, or
rank features into a decision matrix, read and follow the full skill at
`skill/competitive-feature-matrix/SKILL.md` and its `references/` files.

Do not work from memory — the scoring rubric and output format are precise.

Mandatory steps from the skill:
- Ask the scoping questions first: product, segment, core customer problem,
  competitors to be sure to include, and any specific feature to force-validate.
- Present the discovered competitor list and WAIT for the user to approve or
  edit it before analyzing any features. This gate is not optional.
- Output the full marked matrix: one row per feature, every competitor marked
  (with the user's own product flagged), a one-line description per feature, the
  five scores, the priority score, and a verdict — preceded by a plain-language
  "how to read this matrix" block usable by a PM at any level.
- Force any user-named feature into the matrix as its own row, even at 0%
  adoption, so it can be validated against the market.
